This could be a problem with the RAM usage, maybe try using the OpenGL Mode for KSP, that fixed similar problems for me in my 32-bit KSP. I created a shortcut like explained in the topic below and it helped a lot.

There is a tutorial on how to do this here: 

If this does not work out then there could be some sort of problem with the KSP settings, they can sometimes cause a Problem like this. SO after you tried the OpenGL Mode and it did nothing you could try to delete the "settings.cfg" file and try to start the game then so it loads the default settings again.

 

I hope one of these things work for you, if not please let me know and maybe I can find a 3rd aproach.

14 hours ago, agent241 said:

0 MB physical memory [1075 MB free].
0 MB paging file [2264 MB free].
0 MB user address space [44 MB free].

Well, there's your problem. No free memory remaining.

As @YTNewneomentioned, you start by forcing the OpenGL mode. If that fails then remove optional part mods. If problems continue, select a lower resolution RSS texture pack and/or lower the in-game texture quality.
